WEBVTT

00:20.503 --> 00:24.058
[ Indistinct whispering ]

00:24.093 --> 00:25.404
WOMAN: And relax.

00:25.439 --> 00:28.200
[ Groans ]

00:35.414 --> 00:37.175
What...

00:42.801 --> 00:45.769
Oh, my God,
it is so good to see you.

00:45.804 --> 00:49.497
Though I wish it was
under better circumstances.

00:49.532 --> 00:51.844
¿Que? Como?

00:51.879 --> 00:53.191
How is this even happening?

00:53.225 --> 00:54.744
You -- You died.

00:54.778 --> 00:57.471
I remember you died
in that car accident with Papi.

00:57.505 --> 00:59.231
I was...I was 14.

00:59.266 --> 01:03.615
You know, that was a, um...

01:03.649 --> 01:06.514
That was a terrible
final memory.

01:06.549 --> 01:08.378
Dime.

01:08.413 --> 01:10.173
I've never seen Mami
so devastated.

01:12.727 --> 01:14.902
Though she hated
when Papi let us visit you.

01:14.936 --> 01:16.628
She thought being around you
would make us gay.

01:16.662 --> 01:18.319
Make you gay.

01:18.354 --> 01:21.150
[ Laughter ]

01:21.184 --> 01:23.221
Am I dreaming?

01:24.498 --> 01:27.811
This feels so real.

01:27.846 --> 01:31.194
OPHELIA: It is real, baby.

01:31.229 --> 01:33.438
I don't think I know you two,
do I?

01:33.472 --> 01:36.854
Mona, what was the last thing
that you remember?

01:36.889 --> 01:39.547
Um...

01:39.582 --> 01:41.342
we were doing a spell
for Jordan,

01:41.377 --> 01:43.862
and I felt like

01:43.896 --> 01:46.554
I was in some kind of trance.

01:46.589 --> 01:49.729
Wisdom, power, magick spun!

01:49.764 --> 01:52.733
Through the many to the one!

01:57.186 --> 01:59.188
I don't -- I don't really know.

01:59.222 --> 02:04.158
Oh, sweetie, it's alright,
we're here to help.

02:04.193 --> 02:05.884
I'm sorry, who are you?

02:05.918 --> 02:08.473
How are you in mi casa?

02:08.507 --> 02:11.476
Actually, this is our house.

02:11.510 --> 02:12.615
I'm Asha.

02:12.649 --> 02:14.237
This is Ophelia.

02:14.272 --> 02:17.861
You don't know us,
but we're your Guides.

02:21.486 --> 02:23.488
♪ Hey, hey

02:23.522 --> 02:26.836
♪ Hey, hey, hey

02:26.870 --> 02:28.493
TIO MARIO: You're dead.

02:28.527 --> 02:35.258
♪ Hey, hey, hey

02:35.293 --> 02:37.191
♪ Wicked, wicked

02:37.226 --> 02:38.296
♪ Are we

02:38.329 --> 02:40.228
♪ Wicked, wicked, wicked

02:40.263 --> 02:42.748
♪ Are we in a wicked city?

02:42.783 --> 02:44.680
No, no, no, no, no, no.

02:44.716 --> 02:45.855
This can't be right.

02:45.889 --> 02:47.270
Call 911!

02:47.305 --> 02:48.547
Why -- How did this even happen?

02:48.582 --> 02:50.653
Yo, we have to call Tabitha.

02:50.687 --> 02:51.895
What? No, Sherise!

02:51.930 --> 02:53.483
Tabitha didn't even
want me to do

02:53.518 --> 02:55.520
the amplification spell
in the first place.

02:55.554 --> 02:58.799
Jordan, Mona is dead,

02:58.833 --> 03:00.939
and you're worried about getting
in trouble with Tabitha?

03:00.973 --> 03:02.803
Yo, someone call 911!

03:02.837 --> 03:04.701
And tell them what, Camille?

03:04.736 --> 03:06.772
That our friend died
in a magick spell?

03:06.807 --> 03:08.636
They'll think we killed her
and they'll arrest us all.

03:08.671 --> 03:10.845
We did kill her!
Make the damn call

03:10.880 --> 03:13.296
and maybe they'll get here fast
enough so they can save her.

03:13.331 --> 03:15.678
Camille, you just said it.

03:15.712 --> 03:17.680
We killed her.

03:17.714 --> 03:19.923
With magick.

03:19.958 --> 03:24.583
And there ain't nothing you or I
or any doctor can do about it.

03:24.618 --> 03:26.654
You gotta stop this, girl.

03:26.689 --> 03:29.485
Let her go.

03:29.519 --> 03:31.728
No. No, no, no.
Camille, Camille,

03:31.763 --> 03:33.316
why are you stopping?

03:33.351 --> 03:34.766
Camille!

03:34.800 --> 03:37.769
CAMILLE: She's right, Angela.

03:37.803 --> 03:39.011
Mona is gone.

03:39.046 --> 03:40.530
[ Crying ] No.

03:40.565 --> 03:42.498
I'm so sorry.

03:42.531 --> 03:44.362
Friend, I'm so sorry.

03:44.396 --> 03:47.641
So sorry.

03:47.675 --> 03:49.505
How did I know that, thought?

03:49.539 --> 03:51.576
I felt this.

03:51.610 --> 03:53.992
But why?

03:54.026 --> 03:55.890
I killed her! I...

03:55.925 --> 03:59.653
[ Crying ]

03:59.687 --> 04:04.692
Wait, wait, I-I-I can fix this.

04:06.591 --> 04:09.041
I know how to bring her back!

04:11.043 --> 04:13.770
Come on.

04:13.805 --> 04:17.601
[ Crying ]

04:17.636 --> 04:20.673
[ Dramatic music plays ]

04:35.896 --> 04:38.070
No, no, that doesn't make sense.

04:38.105 --> 04:41.073
This is a dream
or a nightmare.

04:41.108 --> 04:43.386
A quirky nightmare.

04:43.421 --> 04:45.802
She's doing better
than I thought she would.

04:45.837 --> 04:47.701
It's okay, darling.
Keep breathing.

04:47.735 --> 04:49.841
Keep breathing?
No, start talking!

04:49.875 --> 04:51.325
What the fuck is going on here?!

04:51.360 --> 04:54.086
-Language!
-Mona, you and your friends

04:54.121 --> 04:58.090
were messing with a power
that's too big for you.

04:58.125 --> 05:00.507
Too big and too dangerous.

05:00.541 --> 05:01.887
A power none of you know about.

05:01.922 --> 05:03.544
What does that mean?

05:03.579 --> 05:06.823
[ Speaks Spanish ]
It was an amplification spell.

05:06.858 --> 05:08.066
Ha! If only.

05:08.100 --> 05:11.863
Asha, hush.

05:11.897 --> 05:15.832
Mona, dear, that new friend
of yours, Camille?

05:15.867 --> 05:17.455
[ Laughs ] Whew!

05:17.489 --> 05:19.388
She has got a lot of power,

05:19.422 --> 05:21.735
but not a damn clue
what to do with it.

05:21.769 --> 05:23.426
Dangerous power.

05:23.461 --> 05:24.427
Dangerous?

05:27.154 --> 05:30.364
The spell you did caused
a strong surge of power,

05:30.399 --> 05:32.401
and you essentially
short-circuited.

05:32.435 --> 05:35.127
Like when you blow the power
out of a building.

05:35.162 --> 05:37.371
You're that building, mami.

05:37.406 --> 05:40.167
So now, dear, you're dead.

05:40.201 --> 05:43.170
[ Breathing shakily ]

05:43.204 --> 05:46.415
[ Dramatic music plays ]

05:51.040 --> 05:54.871
Darletra, be a dear

05:54.906 --> 05:58.081
and remove your brother's body.

05:58.116 --> 06:02.983
He doesn't exactly go
with the ritual decor.

06:03.017 --> 06:06.055
[ Dramatic music plays ]

06:16.859 --> 06:18.481
I've seen the spell.

06:18.516 --> 06:19.758
Girl, please tell me you not

06:19.793 --> 06:21.070
talking about
a resurrection spell.

06:21.104 --> 06:22.899
That's exactly
what I'm talking about.

06:22.934 --> 06:24.763
Wait, wait, wait, she serious?

06:24.798 --> 06:27.490
There's really a spell that can
bring people back from the dead?

06:27.525 --> 06:28.664
Unfortunately, yes.

06:28.698 --> 06:31.045
And it could be very dangerous.

06:31.080 --> 06:32.633
I know I seen it somewhere.

06:32.668 --> 06:35.981
It think it was like a --
a brown book, black book.

06:36.016 --> 06:37.673
Angela, what the --

06:37.707 --> 06:38.777
I don't think
this is a good idea.

06:38.812 --> 06:41.055
This is a terrible idea.

06:41.090 --> 06:43.575
Look, even if
you found the spell,

06:43.610 --> 06:45.058
we ain't got the kind of power.

06:45.094 --> 06:46.820
And it's dangerous
if we fuck it up.

06:46.854 --> 06:48.511
Sherise, please!

06:48.546 --> 06:51.825
Mona died because of something
I begged her to do!

06:51.859 --> 06:54.137
I can't lose her.

06:54.172 --> 06:55.898
We got to at least try.

06:57.555 --> 06:59.626
Look, Mona was my friend too.

06:59.659 --> 07:02.180
But you don't know
what you'll be bringing back.

07:02.214 --> 07:04.941
Wait, what do you mean?

07:04.976 --> 07:07.875
You think Mona's there
by herself?

07:07.910 --> 07:10.568
There's other people
and entities and spirits.

07:10.602 --> 07:12.708
All things that don't belong
in this world.

07:12.742 --> 07:15.676
Any of them
can come through with her.

07:15.711 --> 07:17.678
Yo, this is crazy.
Guys, we can't --

07:17.713 --> 07:20.785
Thank you, Camille!
Someone sees sense.

07:25.099 --> 07:26.618
Y'all hear that?

07:26.653 --> 07:28.931
Hear what?

07:28.965 --> 07:31.865
Nothing, nothing, never mind.

07:31.899 --> 07:35.593
[ Indistinct whispering ]

07:35.627 --> 07:39.079
[ Dramatic music plays ]

07:39.113 --> 07:42.841
Dang it. Where is this book?

07:54.819 --> 07:55.992
Hey, did you find out
anything about Kendria Sullivan?

08:00.859 --> 08:03.759
Well, cause of death?

08:03.793 --> 08:06.520
A single stab wound
to the abdomen.

08:06.555 --> 08:09.316
So what are they thinking?
Are they thinking premeditated?

08:09.350 --> 08:10.835
No?

08:10.869 --> 08:13.734
What, was it a home invasion
gone wrong?

08:13.769 --> 08:15.598
Oh.

08:15.633 --> 08:19.050
Was there anything unusual
about the crime scene?

08:19.084 --> 08:21.328
Uh-huh.

08:21.362 --> 08:22.985
Well, how about the body?

08:23.019 --> 08:26.782
Was there anything unusual
or strange?

08:26.816 --> 08:28.956
Okay, nothing. Alright.

08:28.991 --> 08:30.889
Well, thanks, Q.

08:30.924 --> 08:33.684
It pays to have friends
in high places.

08:33.720 --> 08:35.238
Alright. Bye.

08:35.273 --> 08:38.309
[ Dramatic music plays ]

08:40.933 --> 08:43.937
Okay, look,
everything came up clean.

08:43.971 --> 08:47.181
So whoever did this
really covered their tracks,

08:47.216 --> 08:51.979
which means we may never know
who found her or why.

08:52.808 --> 08:54.361
Oh, my God.

08:54.395 --> 08:56.915
Oh, my God, I'm dead!

08:56.950 --> 08:59.608
No, no, no, no, no.

08:59.642 --> 09:00.919
I take it back, Ophelia.

09:00.954 --> 09:04.095
She's not handling this so well.

09:04.129 --> 09:07.270
And you were just a beacon
of acceptance when you died?

09:07.305 --> 09:10.170
Mona, dear, you should sit down.

09:10.204 --> 09:11.999
-I need some air!
-We have much to tell you.

09:12.034 --> 09:15.071
ASHA: Ooh, I would advise you
not to do that.

09:15.106 --> 09:16.245
I can't breathe!

09:16.279 --> 09:19.593
Okay, your choice.

09:19.628 --> 09:22.044
Sobrina, sobrina.

09:22.078 --> 09:23.804
[ Gasps ]

09:26.945 --> 09:31.847
Mona, dear, please, you're --
you're disrupting our calm.

09:31.881 --> 09:35.298
Doing good.
Deep breaths in and out.

09:35.333 --> 09:37.956
In and out.

09:37.991 --> 09:40.787
Mona, listen.
We don't have a lot of time.

09:40.821 --> 09:44.894
If magick killed me,
can't magick send me back?

09:44.929 --> 09:46.620
Can you send me back?

09:46.655 --> 09:49.381
No one here can do that.

09:49.415 --> 09:50.831
But your friends are trying.

09:52.833 --> 09:53.903
This is it!

09:53.938 --> 09:55.802
This is the book.

09:55.836 --> 09:59.702
Jordan, you really need to stop.

09:59.737 --> 10:01.359
Okay.

10:04.155 --> 10:06.433
You don't want to do this.

10:06.467 --> 10:09.954
Stop what you're doing.

10:09.988 --> 10:12.888
Close the book.

10:12.922 --> 10:14.165
There's...

10:14.199 --> 10:15.753
something...

10:15.787 --> 10:17.409
There's nothing you need.

10:17.444 --> 10:20.309
Close the book.

10:20.343 --> 10:23.070
Let. Her. Go!

10:25.486 --> 10:27.316
Yo, what the fuck, Sherise!

10:27.350 --> 10:28.973
Stop trying to influence me!

10:29.007 --> 10:30.319
Look, you may have more power

10:30.353 --> 10:32.183
and experience
than the rest of us,

10:32.217 --> 10:34.081
but you can't manipulate people
when you don't get your way.

10:34.116 --> 10:35.289
It's not about
me getting my way.

10:35.324 --> 10:36.946
This is dangerous.

10:36.981 --> 10:39.777
What if you bring back
something that ain't Mona?

10:39.811 --> 10:41.054
Here it is!

10:41.088 --> 10:42.296
Look, look, Sherise,
we can do this.

10:42.331 --> 10:43.884
I have Mona's powers.

10:43.919 --> 10:45.990
Between us and Camille,
we can actually do this.

10:46.024 --> 10:47.474
-Please.
-Yes.

10:47.508 --> 10:50.132
Wait, wait, wait.
Where is Camille?

10:50.165 --> 10:51.340
JORDAN: She has to be close.

10:51.374 --> 10:54.136
I can still feel her.

10:54.170 --> 10:57.208
[ Indistinct whispering ]

11:07.528 --> 11:09.772
CAMILLE: Hello?

11:09.807 --> 11:11.049
Who's there?

11:11.084 --> 11:13.707
WHISPERS: Camille. Save her.

11:13.742 --> 11:18.125
Camille, you can save her.

11:18.160 --> 11:19.886
You must save her.

11:19.920 --> 11:22.233
Save her...

11:22.267 --> 11:24.166
Pomegranate seeds!
That's perfect, Angela.

11:24.200 --> 11:26.893
No, it's not perfect, Angela.

11:26.927 --> 11:30.379
Look, my entire Nigerian
mother's side of the family

11:30.413 --> 11:33.002
has been doing magick
since before slavery.

11:33.037 --> 11:34.383
And we don't even
do death magick.

11:34.417 --> 11:37.489
It's forbidden.

11:37.524 --> 11:40.147
Tabitha warned us about
breaking magickal rules.

11:40.182 --> 11:42.529
And you're about to
break a big one.

11:42.563 --> 11:46.498
[ Dramatic music plays ]

11:46.533 --> 11:48.224
-It's worth it.
-It's worth it.

11:58.579 --> 12:01.513
So, I can go back?

12:01.548 --> 12:06.070
Yes, but resurrection spells
are very dangerous.

12:06.104 --> 12:07.243
Why?

12:07.278 --> 12:09.280
Is something going
to happen to me?

12:09.314 --> 12:11.385
Am I going to come back...
wrong?

12:11.420 --> 12:13.318
When the dark meets the light,

12:13.353 --> 12:17.460
a change comes
that causes sacrifice.

12:17.495 --> 12:19.290
ASHA: Death knocks twice,

12:19.324 --> 12:23.812
taking the soul of the one
everyone is looking for.

12:23.846 --> 12:25.158
What are you talking about?

12:25.192 --> 12:27.505
Nothing you're saying
is making sense.

12:32.993 --> 12:35.099
Mira,listen --
There are certain things

12:35.133 --> 12:37.826
that we can't directly
speak about here.

12:37.860 --> 12:39.310
It's -- It's not allowed.

12:39.344 --> 12:40.449
Not allowed by who?

12:40.483 --> 12:42.140
It doesn't matter.

12:42.175 --> 12:44.453
That's just the way it is,
darling.

12:44.487 --> 12:47.801
We try, but it comes out
in riddles.

12:49.492 --> 12:52.254
Y'all, we can't do the spell
without Mona.

12:52.288 --> 12:53.600
We ain't got that much juice.

12:53.634 --> 12:55.567
I mean, look, it took five of us
to kill her.

12:55.602 --> 12:57.052
Four of us ain't about to
bring her back.

12:57.086 --> 12:59.054
Except I have Mona's powers now.

12:59.088 --> 13:02.195
And I can make a potion that
will enhance our natural powers.

13:02.229 --> 13:04.231
It won't last long,
but it'll open us up

13:04.266 --> 13:06.613
to a stronger flow
so that her spirit can return.

13:06.647 --> 13:08.304
Everything I need
is downstairs in the shop.

13:08.339 --> 13:10.306
JORDAN: Come on.

13:10.341 --> 13:13.378
[ Dramatic music plays ]

13:15.967 --> 13:18.867
Girl, what the fuck
are you doing?

13:20.869 --> 13:23.009
We have to try.

13:23.043 --> 13:24.389
They're right.
We can't do this without you.

13:24.424 --> 13:26.633
You got to be kidding me.

13:26.667 --> 13:31.120
Sherise, I love her.

13:31.155 --> 13:33.536
Please.

13:33.571 --> 13:37.092
She died because of me.

13:37.126 --> 13:39.301
I can't fix this without you.

13:44.478 --> 13:46.653
Let me see this damn spell.

13:46.687 --> 13:49.276
Alright.
I'll be back in a jiffy!

13:55.558 --> 13:58.113
I know you are out there.

13:58.147 --> 13:59.977
Show me where you are.

14:00.011 --> 14:03.049
[ Dramatic music plays ]

14:11.609 --> 14:13.542
You need help with anything?

14:13.576 --> 14:15.130
No.

14:15.164 --> 14:18.098
I do these all the time.
It's pretty simple.

14:20.031 --> 14:23.379
Does your family do magick too?

14:23.414 --> 14:25.140
No.

14:25.174 --> 14:29.213
I've had a way with plants
since I was a teen.

14:29.247 --> 14:32.388
I didn't even know it was magick
until Tabitha taught me.

14:32.423 --> 14:35.564
Been practicing ever since.

14:35.598 --> 14:39.568
Can you go get
five pomegranate seeds for me?

14:39.602 --> 14:40.880
Yeah.

14:41.673 --> 14:44.884
[ Somber music plays ]

15:06.698 --> 15:09.356
Thank you.

15:11.013 --> 15:15.121
You really care for her,
don't you?

15:15.155 --> 15:17.019
She's everything.

15:18.987 --> 15:21.541
I've known her forever.

15:21.575 --> 15:27.581
It took her a long time
to open up to be something more.

15:27.616 --> 15:31.344
Oh, you're together.

15:31.378 --> 15:33.070
We're...

15:33.104 --> 15:34.726
involved.

15:34.761 --> 15:37.246
No labels, but...

15:37.281 --> 15:40.284
there's definitely
something special here.

15:43.114 --> 15:47.118
I've never loved anyone
the way I love her.

15:50.018 --> 15:53.055
[ Breathes shakily ]

15:57.128 --> 16:00.718
The way you guys care
for each other...

16:00.752 --> 16:03.583
you're lucky.

16:03.617 --> 16:06.724
I don't really have people
like that.

16:10.486 --> 16:12.109
You will.

16:12.143 --> 16:15.181
[ Dramatic music plays ]

16:31.162 --> 16:33.164
Sanguine sacrificii.

16:33.199 --> 16:35.753
Sanguine sacrificii.

16:35.787 --> 16:39.481
Sanguine sacrificii.

16:45.590 --> 16:48.076
Alright.

16:48.110 --> 16:49.353
We're ready.

16:49.387 --> 16:51.079
We are too.

16:54.082 --> 16:55.635
We're gonna need our blood.

16:55.669 --> 16:58.327
Since we used our blood
in the spell that killed her,

16:58.362 --> 17:00.122
we're gonna need it again
to bring her back.

17:00.157 --> 17:02.124
Yes, and add it to this.

17:02.159 --> 17:04.436
Wait, aren't we
gonna drink that?

17:04.471 --> 17:06.127
This is our best option.

17:06.163 --> 17:07.854
The blood will connect us.

17:07.887 --> 17:11.098
[ Dramatic music plays ]

17:24.595 --> 17:26.734
We need Mona's blood too.

17:28.116 --> 17:30.325
Yes, okay.

17:36.676 --> 17:39.265
Alright.

17:40.680 --> 17:43.165
Okay.

17:49.137 --> 17:50.897
Alright.

17:50.931 --> 17:52.554
Bottoms up.

18:09.536 --> 18:13.264
Um, is this is safe?

18:13.299 --> 18:15.853
Girl, we're about to bring
somebody back from the dead

18:15.887 --> 18:18.752
and you're worried about
if Angela's tea is safe?

18:18.787 --> 18:21.755
She has advanced degrees
in botany and chemistry.

18:21.790 --> 18:25.207
She actually knows
what she's doing.

18:25.242 --> 18:28.107
[ Breathes deeply ]

18:37.288 --> 18:40.222
When your friends try
to take you back,

18:40.257 --> 18:42.500
it's your choice
whether to go or to stay.

18:45.641 --> 18:47.954
I'm not ready to die.

18:47.988 --> 18:49.576
No one ever is.

18:49.611 --> 18:52.200
But returning back
to the living,

18:52.234 --> 18:53.960
it poses its own challenges.

18:53.994 --> 18:56.445
OPHELIA:
Death will follow you back.

18:56.480 --> 18:59.621
And unto your friends
danger shall --

19:02.210 --> 19:04.522
Look, I already know that
you're gonna go back,

19:04.557 --> 19:06.352
so let's just cut to it.

19:06.386 --> 19:08.699
